<br>
The guy in Kaladim is very easy, with 192 pickpocket at level 49 I got behind him, turned on sneak, and just hit pickpocket over and over and over again.  Occasionally he disappears for a bit, but will shortly re-spawn.  It took quite a while for me to get the parchment, but it was shortly after he spawned.  My pickpocket had advanced from 192 to 200 by that point, so I don't know if 200 pp is required to get the parchment.<br>
<br>
The tricky pickpocket is in Neriak, as a follower of Brell, the Dark Elves did not like me.  Using sneak/hide I got to the rogue guild in the 3rd gate just fine.  The tricky part is that slightly behind the npc rogue GM, lie two other dark elves.<br>
<br>
The trick is to turn on sneak/hide and stand on the second step from the top (just barely close enough to pickpocket).  You'll see what I mean when you get there.<br>
<br>
Hit pickpocket and IMMEDIATELY hit hide, I'd reccomend waiting for a second after pickpocket refreshes before attempting again.<br>
<br>
I had to steal all the money from the npc rogue GM and then a few more pickpockets before I got the parchment.<br>
<br>
Good luck to all you other folks! I'm headed off to grab my Book of Souls.<br>
<br>
---- Edit ----<br>
After talking with another Rogue, apparantly I got lucky!<br>
I never got caught pickpocketing in 3-4 hours with Foundy and the 20-30 pickpockets in Neriak.  Also it seems it took an abnormally small amount of time for me.  Luck of the midgets!<br>
Gnidget<br>
Povar Server <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ufoomkin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>foomkin</A> at: 11/28/01 1:22:38 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/umenamino.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Menamino </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/27/01 11:14:33 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pick Pocket Tips for Epic</span><hr size=1> thanks ;D <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ujokerale.showPublicProfile?language=EN>jokerale</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/dagger.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 8:08:51 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pick Pocket Tips for Epic</span><hr size=1> My first run at getting the bottom parchment from Tani N'Mar ended up bloody, even using sneak, as he aggro'd on me after two consecutive empty picks. Being a DE, I just took the beating to avoid the faction hit. Once rezzed, I went through the next 2 respawns resetting sneak in between each pick and he never aggro'd. Maybe I just got lucky, but that tactic seemed to work well. Got the parchment on that third spawn. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
~Praalos Bladebane<br>
  51 Rake of Povar<br>
  Twists of Fate<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/usilvorn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silvorn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 11:12:03 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pick Pocket Tips for Epic</span><hr size=1> Founy depops once per day at 8am game time and respawns at 10am. Tani depops and respawns 4 or 5 times between 8pm and 10pm. So 8-10 PM  you can get shots at 4 or 5 of him in a short itme. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uduloktherogue.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Dulok the Rogue</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 11:17:53 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pick Pocket Tips for Epic</span><hr size=1> If you have never killed DE's the DE mask should take you to indiff with 3rd gate. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzardossk.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zardossk</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/28/01 11:42:58 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Pick Pocket Tips for Epic</span><hr size=1> I just did this with my rogue about four weeks ago, get the loc of Tani, then go outside and on top of the rogue building to the same loc. The vertical part in the loc doesnt count in PP, it will give you a message that you are too far away but will still allow you to pickpocket him. Also, I suggest getting a SoW outside of Neriak and hightailing it in to the rogue guild, stand on top of the building, facing the way out, the position facing doesnt matter with PP either, if you see NPCs running out of the building after a failed PP, book it to the zone. It took me 2 spawns of him to get the note, altho I had 200 PP skill when i did it. If you get 3 or so PPs with nothing, stop and wait for a respawn. I had him aggro on me once, but was able to make it to the zone. Also if you have a friend to help ya, have him/her stand right next to Tani and if he moves to go after you, have the friend alert you asap, that way you get a head start to the zone. <br>
<br>
Founy is a little easier, stand just close enough to PP him(between him and the zone), then turn towards the zone and PP away.  Again if you get 3 or more tries with nothing returned, stop and wait for him to despawn and re-spawn.  It took 12 spawns before he gave me the note.  SoW helps alot too but is not necessary cause the zone is very close.<br>
<br>
I just recently killed Renux and Phinny for the KK robe, now the only thing left is the General (and yes I know the General can drop the Quill, if he does, another rogue in my guild can have it) hope this helps...<br>
<br>
Denzr Merquise<br>
50th rogue of the<br>
-Brothers of Darkness-<br>
